587
00:59:30,431 --> 00:59:38,453
[SPEAKER_02]: And so that may not be the purpose or intent of the policy, but something has to help people with a clear path.

588
00:59:39,946 --> 00:59:50,171
[SPEAKER_02]: at a time when something traumatic is happening, either to them or their child, to say, like, if I do this, the right next steps will happen.

589
00:59:50,191 --> 00:59:56,274
[SPEAKER_02]: And I won't fall into a situation where I did the wrong thing because I thought I did the right thing.

590
00:59:56,314 --> 01:00:02,817
[SPEAKER_02]: And so I think it doesn't, I think in the policy, this language is fine, but in the, like,

591
01:00:03,565 --> 01:00:22,154
[SPEAKER_02]: parent facing simple flow chart, that needs to be really clear to them so that they're not working harder to figure out how to tell somebody something's going wrong than they are about taking care of their child, for example, or making sure there's some immediate action happening.

592
01:00:22,214 --> 01:00:26,155
[SPEAKER_02]: So I think those two documents, they don't have to say exactly the same thing.

593
01:00:26,195 --> 01:00:27,756
[SPEAKER_02]: They can be for different purposes.

594
01:00:28,316 --> 01:00:31,738
[SPEAKER_02]: But I do think one of those documents, I think the flow chart,

595
01:00:32,269 --> 01:00:41,552
[SPEAKER_02]: has to be crystal clear for parents about what to do and who they can expect to respond when they raise an issue.

596
01:00:42,433 --> 01:00:50,776
[SPEAKER_02]: Because I think what I've heard again and again from parents who have been in this situation is they all thought they did the right thing.

597
01:00:51,896 --> 01:00:56,258
