627
01:03:02,131 --> 01:03:08,716
[SPEAKER_10]: So I think we have to think about how we state that and maybe it's after this.

628
01:03:08,956 --> 01:03:11,698
[SPEAKER_10]: If, I don't know, I just wanna put that in the parking lot.

629
01:03:15,407 --> 01:03:16,849
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you, Dr. Kay.

630
01:03:18,571 --> 01:03:29,704
[SPEAKER_04]: So I just want to, when we're talking about timelines, I think it's very important for us to keep in mind too, I don't know about the high school and the junior high level, but it is incredibly time consuming.

631
01:03:30,648 --> 01:03:38,093
[SPEAKER_04]: for the, at least at the Missotok, from the point of when it arrives on our desk to when we get it done.

632
01:03:38,894 --> 01:03:43,957
[SPEAKER_04]: Because oftentimes we're investigating and we talk to one child and that leads us to four more.

633
01:03:44,598 --> 01:03:50,222
[SPEAKER_04]: And then those four, it's like the Fabergé commercial, you tell two and they'll tell two and so on and so on, if you remember that.

634
01:03:50,802 --> 01:03:51,563
[SPEAKER_04]: years gone by.

635
01:03:52,243 --> 01:04:06,973
[SPEAKER_04]: And so I mean literally when I got back from my leave, I had nothing but bullying reports on my desk and not all of them were founded, but that's all I was doing pretty much when I got back here, because we talked to kids at length, we try not to put words into their mouth, they're little,

636
01:04:07,703 --> 01:04:13,589
[SPEAKER_04]: You know, they sometimes don't really fully understand, although many times it does happen that it is bullying.

637
01:04:13,689 --> 01:04:17,633
[SPEAKER_04]: So I just, I think we need to be cautious when we're putting timelines.

638
01:04:17,733 --> 01:04:22,117
[SPEAKER_04]: I think it's important to say from the time we get it, that the investigation starts.

639
01:04:22,738 --> 01:04:31,347
[SPEAKER_04]: But from that point on to me, it's really worrying and it makes my job even harder to say that, you know, we have to start investigating and be done within three weeks.

640
01:04:32,273 --> 01:04:38,819
[SPEAKER_04]: You know, because sometimes vacations come in between, especially if we're talking about having us have to deal with it over the summer, right?

641
01:04:39,019 --> 01:04:39,720
[SPEAKER_04]: Does that make sense?

642
01:04:41,141 --> 01:04:42,102
[SPEAKER_08]: Absolutely makes sense.

643
01:04:42,142 --> 01:04:42,322
[SPEAKER_08]: Yes.

644
01:04:42,362 --> 01:04:42,963
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you for that.

645
01:04:42,983 --> 01:04:43,964
[SPEAKER_08]: I think that's really important.

646
01:04:45,045 --> 01:04:56,195
[SPEAKER_08]: You know, and I think when I think about timelines, I think of, I think of having an understanding as the person who's waiting

647
01:04:58,101 --> 01:05:08,186
[SPEAKER_08]: an expectation of when you would reach out and say, did something get lost or forgotten?

648
01:05:09,627 --> 01:05:18,011
[SPEAKER_08]: Rather than on this date and time, it should have been resolved and it isn't, so I should then call the superintendent.

649
01:05:19,231 --> 01:05:26,515
[SPEAKER_08]: But the parent, for instance, might have no idea that when there's a bullying report,

650
01:05:27,049 --> 01:05:32,050
[SPEAKER_08]: that it might take a couple of days or more.

651
01:05:32,931 --> 01:05:36,032
[SPEAKER_08]: So when is the parent supposed to say like, okay, it's been too long?

652
01:05:36,632 --> 01:05:46,335
[SPEAKER_08]: Because I think if the parent doesn't know it's been too long, then they're gonna add to your burden by communicating early over and over again.

653
01:05:47,918 --> 01:05:51,420
[SPEAKER_08]: And that I think is why setting expectations is so important.

654
01:05:51,520 --> 01:05:57,764
[SPEAKER_08]: It's like, okay, like you get a colonoscopy and it's gonna be two days before you get your results.

655
01:05:58,385 --> 01:06:07,591
[SPEAKER_08]: So you don't call your doctor four times the first day and four times the next day, because you've been told it's gonna be a couple of days, but it's been two months.

656
01:06:09,372 --> 01:06:14,195
[SPEAKER_08]: That's a problem, but that would only happen if nobody told you the expectation.

657
01:06:14,715 --> 01:06:17,197
[SPEAKER_08]: So I think that when I think about a timeline, I think of,

658
01:06:18,969 --> 01:06:21,050
[SPEAKER_08]: the expectations that people will have.

659
01:06:22,131 --> 01:06:23,591
[SPEAKER_08]: Member McLaughlin.

660
01:06:25,312 --> 01:06:25,672
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you.

661
01:06:25,792 --> 01:06:35,136
[SPEAKER_10]: I would agree with that, that there should be some response timeline at least, but I also would imagine that there's gonna be some legal timeline.

662
01:06:36,117 --> 01:06:36,357
[SPEAKER_10]: No?

663
01:06:37,777 --> 01:06:43,980
[SPEAKER_08]: I believe there is something in here about how the law does have something.

664
01:06:45,370 --> 01:06:46,731
[SPEAKER_08]: I won't dig into it right now.

665
01:06:46,751 --> 01:06:50,033
[SPEAKER_08]: But yes, obviously, whatever we set for timelines has to fit within the law.

666
01:06:50,073 --> 01:06:52,575
[SPEAKER_08]: And I think Howard will be helpful in that.

667
01:06:53,936 --> 01:06:54,516
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you for that.

668
01:06:54,556 --> 01:06:55,577
[SPEAKER_08]: That's a really excellent point.

669
01:06:55,897 --> 01:06:56,377
[SPEAKER_08]: Member Graham.

670
01:06:57,918 --> 01:07:09,445
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah, I feel pretty strongly that there have to be timelines of some kind in some way, for all the reasons that Member Rousseau describes, but also because

671
01:07:12,564 --> 01:07:19,025
[SPEAKER_02]: It's reasonable in life to expect there to be an expectation of how long something's going to take.

672
01:07:19,245 --> 01:07:20,966
[SPEAKER_02]: Like that is the world that we live in.

673
01:07:21,866 --> 01:07:29,068
[SPEAKER_02]: And I think it's also important for us to acknowledge that we haven't always done this all that well.

674
01:07:29,808 --> 01:07:40,530
[SPEAKER_02]: And in order to like earn the trust of the public, we have to set forth a parameter of how we intend to operate so that they know

675
01:07:41,391 --> 01:07:47,075
[SPEAKER_02]: so that if something goes awry, that we can be alerted that something has gone awry.

676
01:07:47,215 --> 01:07:55,202
[SPEAKER_02]: Because I think that there are times that we're not alerted that things go awry, because everybody thinks somebody knows something about it, and that's maybe not true.

677
01:07:55,762 --> 01:08:02,587
[SPEAKER_02]: So I do think for the efficacy of the process, there has to be a timeline as an important check and balance.

678
01:08:02,988 --> 01:08:09,813
[SPEAKER_02]: But I think that timeline can be written such that if there is more time needed to properly investigate,

679
01:08:10,554 --> 01:08:19,622
[SPEAKER_02]: That is an acceptable thing to have happen, but we have to be able to explain to somebody reading this document why that would be.

680
01:08:19,822 --> 01:08:31,391
[SPEAKER_02]: Like most people, when something happens to their child, they think like this is going to be arbitrated, especially at elementary school, like immediately in the classroom by the teacher the next day, done.

681
01:08:31,411 --> 01:08:39,058
[SPEAKER_02]: And that's not the reality, but I think we've never done a good job of educating people at just how time consuming these things are.

682
01:08:39,650 --> 01:08:45,175
